This paper deals with the optimization of wireless cellular resources in small cell networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The proposed self-organizing scheme also involves system-level control and coordination, which falls under the category of systems and control (SY). Additionally, the paper uses simulations to evaluate the performance of the proposed algorithm, which involves multimedia (MM) applications. Finally, the use of autonomous learning and optimization techniques suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (AI).
